VSaaS (within pipeline) – checks vs blocking
What we check for:
All identified vulnerabilities across severity levels (Critical, High, Medium, etc.)
Exploitability classification (e.g. GEM / exploitable CVEs)
Malware-related findings (where identified by Aqua scanning)
What triggers FAIL (VTM validation):
VSaaS marks VTM VALIDATION = FAIL where exploitable vulnerabilities are present (e.g. GEM or exploitable CVEs)
This is reflected in the scan report status
What we block for (current behaviour):
Pipeline gating is aligned to VTM VALIDATION status
Images with FAIL status (i.e. exploitable vulnerabilities) are blocked from promotion
Malware handling:
Malware-type findings (e.g. MAL classification) appear to be treated as exploitable vulnerabilities by Aqua
As a result, they contribute to a FAIL status indirectly
There is no separate/explicit malware-only blocking control (i.e. not independently enforced outside exploitability criteria)
